    "A node which has multiple parents is known as a collider.",
    "The configuration shown in Fig. 2c, where B is a collider, and there is no edge between A and C, will be referred to here as a v-structure, although other authors use the term unshielded collider.",
    "Probabilistic graphical models represent conditional independence through the notion of graphical separation.",
    "For example, Cancer \"separates\" Smoker from XRay in the graph in Fig. 1.",
    "DAGs use a special form of graphical separation known as d-separation P(XRay|Cancer, Smoker) = P(XRay|Cancer) XRay ⟂ Smoker|Cancer."
